## Part I

### 1. Dataset Construction

We use four monthly U.S. series from 1985M1 to 2023M3:

- **EPU**: News-Based Policy Uncertainty Index in levels, from policyuncertainty.com
- **PAYEMS**: Nonfarm payroll employment, seasonally adjusted, converted to month-on-month growth rates: $100 \times (X_t / X_{t-1} - 1)$
- **INDPRO**: Industrial production index, seasonally adjusted, same transformation
- **PCEPI**: PCE price index, seasonally adjusted, same transformation

After taking growth rates, the usable sample starts at 1985M2 (458 observations).

![The four panels show the raw level series from 1985M1 to 2023M3. Top left: PCEPI, with a steady upward trend and some acceleration after 2020. Top right: PAYEMS (thousands of persons), with long-run employment growth and clear drops during the 2008--2009 recession and the COVID-19 shock in 2020. Bottom left: INDPRO, with similar cyclical patterns. Bottom right: the EPU index in levels, with high volatility and a large spike around the COVID-19 pandemic. PAYEMS, INDPRO, and PCEPI from FRED; EPU from policyuncertainty.com.](output/data_figure.png){width=65%}

